"48:6:2" : {s: 48, a: 6, w: 2, r: "نفق", t: "ٱلْمُنَٰفِقِينَ", l: "مُنَٰفِقُون", lc: 27, tl: "l-munāfiqīna", lb: "খরচকারী, ব্যয়কারী",e: "the hypocrite men", b: "মুনাফিকদেরকে", i: "orang-orang munafik laki-laki", f: 15, rm: "to be saleable, to come out of a hole, be exhausted (store), consumed, spent, expenditure. To enter into another hole where there is another outlet, so is a hypocrite who professes to believe first one thing and then another, thus entering faith through one door and leaving it through another.", ag: "ال التعريف وأسم فاعل", eg: "Determiner al and Noun Active participle", tag: "N", pos: "N", att: "ACT_PCPL", qual: "ACC", deg: "", gen: "M", num: "P", mood: "", lu: "أَنفَقَ،مُنَٰفِقُونَ"},
